00:00:07.830 --> 00:00:10.330
This week we have a giveaway.

00:00:10.330 --> 00:00:14.940
And this time it is the Knitter's Pride Nova
Interchangeable Starter set.

00:00:14.940 --> 00:00:16.920
And it's a set like this.

00:00:16.920 --> 00:00:21.320
And it's a set that comes with three different
needle tips, and two needle cord lengths.

00:00:21.320 --> 00:00:26.680
And I'll give you the sizes here -- this is
US sizes 6, 8, and 10.

00:00:26.680 --> 00:00:33.030
Or metric sizes 4.0, 5.0. and 6.0 mm.

00:00:33.030 --> 00:00:37.930
And the starter sets or sampler sets that
Knitter's Pride puts out are such a great

00:00:37.930 --> 00:00:42.870
way to test out different needle materials
when you're looking at investing in an entire

00:00:42.870 --> 00:00:44.980
interchangeable needle set.

00:00:44.980 --> 00:00:49.379
And whether you win this set or not, I really
encourage you to test out needles like this

00:00:49.379 --> 00:00:52.210
before you invest in an interchangeable needle
set.

00:00:52.210 --> 00:00:56.000
Because they are expensive, and you want to
love what you end up getting.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:01.220
Now to back up, what I'm talking about when
I say interchangeable needle set are a set

00:01:01.220 --> 00:01:07.341
of needles that range in, a big range of sizes,
that are the needle tips like this, that come

00:01:07.341 --> 00:01:09.280
with the cord like this.

00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:14.620
So you attach the cord length that you need
to a needle size that you need, and you have

00:01:14.620 --> 00:01:18.550
a huge range -- you end up having hundreds
and hundreds of dollars worth of needles in

00:01:18.550 --> 00:01:21.960
this one set that you spent much less on.

00:01:21.960 --> 00:01:25.740
And I always try to convince new knitters
that are excited about knitting to invest

00:01:25.740 --> 00:01:28.170
in one of those sets, but it's tough, because
you're not sure.

00:01:28.170 --> 00:01:33.100
There are acrylic, and metal, and wood -- and
you don't really know until you try them what's

00:01:33.100 --> 00:01:35.250
going to be appropriate for you.

00:01:35.250 --> 00:01:39.600
Now the Nova needle set is made of nickel
plated brass.

00:01:39.600 --> 00:01:43.200
And these are the slickest, the fastest needles.

00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:46.690
And these needles are most appropriate for
two different kinds of knitters.

00:01:46.690 --> 00:01:50.950
The first kind is, regardless of skill level,
tight knitters.

00:01:50.950 --> 00:01:55.550
If you, maybe you don't even know you're a
tight knitter, but if the stitches don't move

00:01:55.550 --> 00:01:59.690
easily across the needle, or if you're having
a really difficult time getting your needle

00:01:59.690 --> 00:02:02.800
into the next stitch, chances are that you're
a tight knitter.

00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:06.390
So you're going to benefit from the slickness
of these needles.

00:02:06.390 --> 00:02:10.149
The second kind of knitter who will benefit
from these needles are really experienced

00:02:10.149 --> 00:02:11.149
knitters.

00:02:11.149 --> 00:02:16.290
If you rarely have a problem with stitches
falling off the end of the needle accidentally,

00:02:16.290 --> 00:02:21.170
then you have the skills you need to be able
to work with needles this fast.

00:02:21.170 --> 00:02:22.980
That's what they are.

00:02:22.980 --> 00:02:28.240
Tight knitters, experienced knitters, needles
like this will improve your speed.

00:02:28.240 --> 00:02:30.020
And they're fun to use, I think.

00:02:30.020 --> 00:02:33.480
So the next question is, what do I prefer?

00:02:33.480 --> 00:02:37.370
These needles are my go-to needles for almost
everything.

00:02:37.370 --> 00:02:42.330
I go back and forth between Knitter's Pride
Symfonie Dreamz wood needles, which are highly

00:02:42.330 --> 00:02:44.730
laminated wood needles, and these needles.

00:02:44.730 --> 00:02:46.360
I like both of them.

00:02:46.360 --> 00:02:47.360
I like the feeling.

00:02:47.360 --> 00:02:50.540
Kind of just depends on the stickiness of
the yarn, what I like to use.

00:02:50.540 --> 00:02:51.740
I like variety, I guess.

00:02:51.740 --> 00:02:55.550
But really, most things I knit are on these
kind of needles.

00:02:55.550 --> 00:02:58.580
And the tips, I would say, are medium sharp.

00:02:58.580 --> 00:03:01.900
They are good all purpose needle tips.

00:03:01.900 --> 00:03:08.340
Maybe not the best if you are working a complicated
lace pattern, where you have complicated decreases,

00:03:08.340 --> 00:03:10.790
like purling three through the back loop,
or something.

00:03:10.790 --> 00:03:13.310
You might want sharper needles for that.

00:03:13.310 --> 00:03:14.980
But, good all purpose tips.

00:03:14.980 --> 00:03:19.610
So, I'm going to show you how, if you've never
used an interchangeable set, how to attach

00:03:19.610 --> 00:03:20.610
the cords.

00:03:20.610 --> 00:03:23.790
Let's go ahead and take a look.

00:03:23.790 --> 00:03:25.530
So here I have the tips.

00:03:25.530 --> 00:03:27.260
And here I have the cord.

00:03:27.260 --> 00:03:31.310
And the set comes with a couple of these little
keys, like this.

00:03:31.310 --> 00:03:36.330
And the way this works is, you take the cord,
and the cord is threaded.

00:03:36.330 --> 00:03:41.879
So the needle goes on there, and you just
twist it in place.

00:03:41.879 --> 00:03:44.860
And you hand twist it, about as tight as it
will go.

00:03:44.860 --> 00:03:48.630
And the key is here, only to give you something
to hang on to.

00:03:48.630 --> 00:03:51.910
So you can tighten it the rest of the way.

00:03:51.910 --> 00:03:56.901
It might not show up on camera, but there
is a tiny hole at the base of the cord, so

00:03:56.901 --> 00:03:58.380
you put your key in there.

00:03:58.380 --> 00:04:01.810
And that gives you something to hang on to,
to just tighten it the rest of the way.

00:04:01.810 --> 00:04:06.800
And then once you have that, you have a really
smooth join, that isn't going to get caught

00:04:06.800 --> 00:04:08.550
on any of your stitches.

00:04:08.550 --> 00:04:12.349
Now we've had Knitter's Pride Interchangeable
needles in videos before, and people were

00:04:12.349 --> 00:04:14.250
